<H2>How To Make Sweet &amp; Sour Mix</H2>
<table border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse: collapse" bordercolor="#111111" width="100%" id="AutoNumber1">
  <tr>
    <td width="100%">Here's an easy recipe for sweet &amp; sour mix used in many cocktails. 
<p><b>Difficulty Level: </b>Easy &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <b>Time Required: </b>5
minutes 
	<HR noshade color="#612B83" size="1">
    <p>
<b>Here's How:</b> </p>
<ol>
  <li>Put one cup of water in a small saucepan.<li>Add one cup of sugar.<li>Heat to a boil while stirring.<li>Reduce heat and continue to stir until the sugar dissolves.
  <li>Add one cup each of lemon and lime juices. Stir.<li>Cool to room temperature.
  <li>Find a clean container.
  <li>Using a funnel, pour liquid into container.
  <li>Seal and store in refrigerator indefinitely.
  <li>Use whenever a recipe calls for sweet and sour mix.<br>
  </li>
</ol>

